conclusion: Consider the forces acting on the objects to determine what will happen.
Objects A and B are moving through the air and will experience air resistance.
Objects C, D, E, F are placed down and will experience the force of gravity.
The force of gravity is calculated using F = mg.
Mass of objects A and B is negligible compared to objects placed down.
Mass of objects C, D, E, F is negligible compared to objects A and B.
The force of air resistance is calculated using F = 1/2 ρv²C.
For objects A and B, air resistance is negligible compared to gravity.
For objects C, D, E, F, air resistance is negligible compared to gravity.
Net force on objects A and B is F_net = mg - 1/2 ρv²C.
Net force on objects C, D, E, F is F_net = mg.
The net force is directed downward due to gravity.
Objects will accelerate downward due to gravity.
Objects A and B will come into contact with objects C, D, E, F due to gravity.
